I move to amend House Bill No. 1421, as follows:
1. On page 2, lines 16-17, by deleting subsection D; and
2. On page 2, line 17 1/2, by adding a new SECTION 2:
“SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 30.17 of Title 4, unless there
is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
The Legislature hereby occupies and preempts the entire field
of legislation in this state prohibiting the retail sale of cats,
dogs, or any other pets to the complete exclusion of any order,
ordinance, or regulation by any municipality or other political
subdivision of this state.”
Renumber subsequent sections
Amend title to conform
